<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <!-- The above 3 meta tags *must* come first in the head; any other head content must come *after* these tags -->
    <meta name="description" content="Scheduly--an app for the awesome ones.">
    <meta name="author" content="Patrick Wee">
    <link rel="icon" href="../../favicon.ico">
    <title>Scheduly</title>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-header">
        <h1>Scheduly</h1>
        <h4>Get stuff done, quickly.</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="lead">You can now easily create workflows for your projects.</p>
    </div>

    <form class="download_csv">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Basic Information</h2>
        <div class="row">
          <div class='col-sm-12'>
            <input type='text' class="form-control input-lg" placeholder="Tell me the name of this Project!" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div class="container milestones">
        <h2>Milestones</h2>
        <% 3.times do |n| %>
          <%= render 'scheduly/milestone', counter: n %>
        <% end %>
      </div>

      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-sm add_milestone">Add another milestone!</button>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div class="container">
        <h2>Next Steps</h2>
        <div class="row">
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li><strong>Download the CSV file.</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Sign-in to your Google Calendar.</strong> You can click <a href="http://calendar.google.com" target="_blank">here</a>. You will be redirected to Google Calendar.
              <li><strong>Create a new calendar.</strong> This will make sure that if you’re done or if you need to edit something in this work plan, it will be easy! To do this, simply go to your Calendars section on the left hand side, click the drop down icon, and select “Create Calendar.”</li>
              <li><strong>Import Calendar.</strong> On left hand side, you will see a group of calendars called “Other Calendars.” Click the drop down icon, and from there, select Import Calendar. Upload the CSV file. Select the calendar you just created.</li>
              <li><strong>DONE!</strong> You have your nice calendar created!</li>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="container">
        <h2>Download</h2>
        <div class="row download">
          <input type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg btn-block download" value="Download">
        </div>
      </div>
    </form>


    <hr>
    <footer>
      <p>&copy; Nusii Engineering Project 2015 | Learn more about Nusii <a href="www.nusii.com" target="_blank">here</a>!</p>
    </footer>

    <script id="milestone_template" type="x-tmpl-mustache">
      <%= render 'scheduly/milestone', counter: '{{counter}}' %>
    </script>

  </body>
</html>